Wow, this place was good!  I had never been here before, and I only even came here because I had a friend with me who is from the midwest. She vouched for this chain of restaurants, I trusted her, and I have no regrets.  It reminds me of Huey Magoo's. Simple fried chicken served with simple sides and some bread. I wish I could go into more detail on it, but there's really not a ton to say. The chicken was fried perfectly, and so were the fries. Nothing was dripping wet in oil. The bread was good, too. I actually won a free bread in a little game they were playing with little pull-off tabs on their cups of soda. That was fun.  The thing that really sets them apart was their sauce. It was a tangy, zingy little sauce, comparable to Zaxby's, but with a little less tang than them. It was delightful. I recommend coming here and trying it out if you've never come here before.
